== Critics == From Hand to Art received support from audiences and positive reviews in online forums. Online commenters praised the programme as being "meaningful" and they did learn more about local handicrafts.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.discuss.com.hk/viewthread.php?tid=20848194&extra&page=1 | title = Three netizens, centralHK, 明年聽日 and chaiwan_886, commented that on Discuss.com.hk 《一手造成》討論區, page 1}}</ref> Some said the programme successfully aroused arouse public's interest in traditional handicrafts such as [[paper crafts]], [[carvings]], [[shadow play]]s and [[cheongsam]] (qipao), while others felt sorry for the sunset of these beautiful arts due to scarce successors.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.discuss.com.hk/viewthread.php?tid=20848194&extra=&page=3 | title = chaiwan_886, a netizen, said it on Discuss.com.hk 《一手造成》討論區, page 3}}</ref> Moreover, audiences admired the lifelong devotion of the art masters to their works. One forum user even asked for the address and contact number of Master Wong, a sewing master featured in episode 12.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://forum.tvb.com/viewtopic.php?f=835&t=213593 | title = One netizen, amyz123, asked for the contact of Master Wong on TVB.com}}</ref>
