'''Nu Afrika Records, LLC''' is a [[Ghanaian]] entertainment company established by rapper/record producer [[Ball J]]. The company is located at Spintex road, [[Accra]]-[[Ghana]]. It is a full service entertainment company housing a record label and a video production company called 36 Men. The company has worked with almost all the top music and movie stars in Ghana and across Africa such as [[Gurunkz|Guru]], [[Kwaw Kese]], [[Sarkodie (rapper)|Sarkodie]], [[Patoranking]], [[Castro (musician)|Castro]], [[Stonebwoy]], [[Stay Jay|Stay J]], [[EL (rapper)|EL]], [[Joey B]], Nhyiraba Kojo, [[R2Bees]], [[Obour]], Yaa Pono, Praye, [[King Ayisoba]], [[Rocky Dawuni]], [[Ben Brako]], [[Kojo Antwi]], [[Hammer of The Last Two|Hammer]], [[Reggie Rockstone]], [[Eddie Watson]], Ingride Alabi, Ivan Quashigah etc.<ref>{{cite web|last1=ArtistTrove|title=NU AFRiKA Records|url=http://www.artisttrove.com/artist/170570456320125/NU+AFRiKA+Records|website=artisttrove.com|accessdate=22 August 2016}}</ref>
==History== Nu Afrika Records was founded by [[Ball J|Albert Hanson]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artisttrove.com/artist/170570456320125/NU+AFRiKA+Records |title=Nu Afrika Records |publisher=Artisttrove |website=artisttrove.com |accessdate=2016-04-09}}</ref> commonly known as [[Ball J]] in 2006. For the past 9 to 10 years the company have been producing, recording and managing most of [[Ghana]]'s prominent [[Hiplife]] and [[Hip hop]] musicians like Guru, Kwaw Kese, Sarkodie etc. Nu Afrika stands for New (Nu) Africa (Afrika). Most songs produced by [[Ball J]] or owned by the record label has the phrase "Take Y'all To Nu Afrika" "This Is Nu Afrika" or "[[Ball J]] Beat" or "[[Ball J]], where is my grammy" "Ball J Beat on it", "Oh my Ball J Beat" or "Weiye [[Ball J]] Beat (This is [[Ball J]]'s Beat) in the song. The company is best known in the early 2007 to late 2009 for camping young talented artists such as Ntelabi, Obrekuo, Torgbe, Ivy, Rose, Shao Qan, Asabia, Screech, Frank P, D’LO, Bubbles, Fargo, Guantoahene, Hoodboy<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artisttrove.com/artist/170570456320125/NU+AFRiKA+Records |title=Nu Afrika Records |publisher=Artisttrove |website=artisttrove.com |accessdate=2016-04-09}}</ref> and putting them together on a song or mixtapes. Nu Afrika Records pride its self in upgrading [[Africa]]n culture and at the same time preserving it through entertainment with their main goal of promoting [[hip hop]] made in [[Ghana]] (GH Rap) for the global audience and hopes to put [[Ghana]] on the [[world map]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.myjoyonline.com/pages/news/200909/35358.php | title = 'Nu Afrika Project' to project Ghanaian Hip hop to the world | first= Dela Ernest | last= Aglanu | publisher=myjoyonline.com | accessdate= 2016-04-09}}</ref> In 2011, Nu Afrika records released "Ya Tia Tia" music video<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/audio/clip.php?ID=4167 | title = Nu Afrika Records - Ya Tia Tia | first= web | last= Ghana | publisher=ghanaweb.com | accessdate= 2016-04-09}}</ref> which got nominated that same year for best special effect and best [[hip hop]] video in the 4syte music video awards.<ref>{{cite web|title=4syte TV Music Video Awards Nomination List|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/artikel.php?ID=222387 | accessdate= 2016-04-09}}</ref>
==Achievements== Nu Afrika Records is also involved in various media activities like advertisement and jingles for radio and television stations, radio Dj’s, television presenters, companies and events in [[Ghana]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=ArtistTrove|title=NU AFRiKA Records|url=http://www.artisttrove.com/artist/170570456320125/NU+AFRiKA+Records|website=artisttrove.com/|accessdate=22 August 2016}}</ref> The company has worked with top radio stations like, [[List of radio stations in Greater Accra Region|Peace FM]], [[List of radio stations in Greater Accra Region|Joy FM]], [[List of radio stations in Greater Accra Region|Green FM]], [[List of radio stations in Greater Accra Region|Adom FM]], [[List of radio stations in Greater Accra Region|Happy FM]], [[List of radio stations in Greater Accra Region|HITZ FM]], [[List of radio stations in Greater Accra Region|YFM]], [[List of radio stations in Greater Accra Region|XFM]], [[List of radio stations in Greater Accra Region|Radio Gold]], [[List of radio stations in Greater Accra Region|OK FM]], [[List of radio stations in Greater Accra Region|SENA Radio]], [[List of radio stations in Greater Accra Region|CHOICE FM]], [[List of radio stations in Greater Accra Region|Live FM]] and many more. The company also run jingles for companies like JA Plant Pool, [[Ticket Ghana]], [[MTV Base]] News, General Motors, [[Ghana Movie Awards]], Spirited Actor, Green TV and many more. Nu Afrika Records has successfully run jingles for events in [[Ghana]] like, Rick Ross in [[Ghana]] 2010, Sonnie Badu in [[Ghana]] 2010, Cece Winans in [[Ghana]], Scientific Concert 2010, Filla Stone Entertainment events and many more. Nu Afrika has also run jingles for top presenters in [[Ghana]] like Abeku Santana, DJ Black, DJ Bongo, DJ Champagne, DJ Knuckles, Jeremy, Jessica, Brown Berry and many more. Almost all the radio jiggles on [[Ghana]] radio stations are done by [[Ball J]]. [[Ball J]] is also responsible for producing almost all the sound tracks used in [[Ghana]]'s YOLO TV series.
